UYO – The Akwa Ibom State Police Command has announced the arrest of a fake female Constable, one Miss Caroline Udeme, a 24-year-old with Police uniform and Identity card. The fake female Constable had reportedly defrauded one Loveth Ifechineke and Joy Joseph of the sum of N500,000 at Itam market, in Itu local government area of the state. Operatives of the Anti-Child Theft of the Akwa Ibom State Police command have also rescued a 4years old girl, Aisha Rayanu, who was abducted from the Methodist Township Primary school, located at No 34 Chubb road, Ikot Ekpene local government area of the state. The Police Public Relations Officer, Odiko Macdon who paraded the suspects during a press briefing at the state police headquarters, Ikot Akpanabia, Uyo described the incidents as unfortunate, adding that all the suspects will be charged to court as soon as investigations are completed. “On 15/3/2022, at about 1816hrs one Miss Caroline Udeme of Idoro road, Uyo 24-years old, was arrested in police Constable uniform along with a police identity card, suspect has defrauded one Loveth Ifechineke and Joy Joseph all of Itam market of cash and items worth over N500,000. All the suspects will have their day in court as soon as investigation is completed,” he said. The police said the child abductor, one Miss Favour Nwachukwu, 20, reportedly stormed the school and abducted victim and took her to Akpabuyo, in Cross River State to her boyfriend, an ex-militant, as a replacement for her own daughter who was also allegedly stolen. Macdon explained that little Aisha was kidnaped on January 18,2022 and taken to a camp at Essighi, Akpabuyu Local Government Area of Cross River State adding that until she was rescued on March 17,2022, her name was changed to Mirabel by her abductors. He said the suspect had confessed to the crime. POLL He also used the occasion to applaud operatives of the command for their intervention, which led to